=== Wikipedia Editing ===
Please help to improve [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/{{project_name_short}} {{project name}} Wikipedia Page] (English). <ref>
Be aware that Tor exit nodes are usually prevented from editing.
</ref> See the [https://forums.whonix.org/t/wikipedia-page-corrections/484 feedback thread] for further information. Or if you speak German, help to keep [https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/{{project_name_short}} {{project name}} German Wikipedia Page] up-to-date.

=== Testing ===
Whonix needs more people to test new {{project name}} features, bug fixes and so on.

* Join us in testing new [[AppArmor]] profiles for improved security! Visit the [https://forums.whonix.org/c/apparmor {{project name}} AppArmor Forum].
* Perform [[Test|numerous activity tests]] on both {{workstation_product_name}} and {{gateway_product_name}}, while running a separate, testers-only {{project name}} version based on the [[{{project name short}}-APT-Repository#Whonix_APT_Repository_Overview|stable-proposed-updates APT repository]].
* Test major, new {{project name}} versions prior to stable release - latest testers-wanted posts can be found here: https://forums.whonix.org/tags/testers-wanted

{{Anchor|Backup Whonix}}

=== Run the {{project name}} Backup Script ===

Create a backup of the {{project name}} Anonymous Operating System website and source code. The more people that retain backups, the less likely {{project name}} can be erased from the history books. This can be done periodically, every now and then or when convenient.

See: [[{{project name short}}BackupScript|How to Backup Whonix]] for further details.

=== Screenshots ===

Whonix requires more recent and awesome [[Screenshots]]. Donate them to {{project name}} or release them into the [https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/ public domain].

=== Videos ===

We need more {{project name}} [[Videos]], particularly in languages other than English. They can be demonstration videos, promotional videos, conceptual videos or tutorials. Donate them to {{project name}} or release them into the [https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/ public domain]. We also have a video script waiting to be produced - please get in contact for further details.

=== Social Media / Marketing ===
Although social media platforms erode privacy goals by collecting a lot of user data, we believe they are important venues for marketing and communication in the modern era.

If you are willing to help or to maintain {{project name}} Twitter, Google+, YouTube or identic.ca accounts or Facebook page, please get in [[Contact|contact]].


